==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, from Old French, from Vulgar Latin ''*vestitura'' "clothing", from Latin [[vestitus]], past participle of [[vestire]] "to clothe", from [[vestis]] "garment".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[covering]] of or like [[clothing]].

===Verb===
{{en-verb|vestur|ing}}

# (''archaic'') To [[clothe]].

